# Font Awesome Pro opt-in (OPTIONAL — the app works fine on Free without this).
#
# The committed project .npmrc deliberately does NOT configure the Pro registry,
# so a tokenless `npm install` succeeds on Free. To pull the Pro icon set instead,
# put these lines in your USER-level ~/.npmrc (NOT the project .npmrc — that one is
# committed and must never carry a token), then set the env var and reinstall:
#
#   # PowerShell:  $env:FONTAWESOME_PACKAGE_TOKEN = "<your-token>"
#   # bash:        export FONTAWESOME_PACKAGE_TOKEN=<your-token>
#   npm install
#
# With this active, npm routes the whole @fortawesome scope to the Pro registry —
# fontawesome-free also resolves there (the Pro registry mirrors Free), which is
# fine because your token authenticates it. copy-web-assets.cjs then prefers the
# Pro package automatically.

@fortawesome:registry=https://npm.fontawesome.com/
//npm.fontawesome.com/:_authToken=${FONTAWESOME_PACKAGE_TOKEN}
